        <obo:IAO_0000115>Adult descending neuron of the posterior brain of the DNp66 group (Berg et al., 2025). It belongs to the VLPl&amp;p2 posterior hemilineage (Berg et al., 2025). It receives input in the ipsilateral superior lateral protocerebrum, gorget, epaulette, vest, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, posterior lateral protocerebrum, superior clamp, inferior clamp and wedge, and the gnathal ganglion, saddle, lower tectulum and abdominal neuromere (Berg et al., 2025). It sends output to the ipsilateral accessory mesothoracic neuropil, flange and T1 leg neuropil, the contralateral accessory mesothoracic neuropil and flange, and the gnathal ganglion, saddle, lower tectulum and abdominal neuromere (Berg et al., 2025). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="http://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2020-07-30T12:00:00Z</terms:date>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>AVLP499</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>DNxn160</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:20000608</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:comment>Cell type identified in multiple EM datasets (Scheffer et al., 2020; Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Marin et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025). Synapse locations are given where each cell of this type in neuprint has at least 10 connections. Hemilineage information from neuprint, though original source not clear.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>adult descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp66</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_20000608"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Adult descending neuron of the posterior brain of the DNp66 group (Berg et al., 2025). It belongs to the VLPl&amp;p2 posterior hemilineage (Berg et al., 2025). It receives input in the ipsilateral superior lateral protocerebrum, gorget, epaulette, vest, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, posterior lateral protocerebrum, superior clamp, inferior clamp and wedge, and the gnathal ganglion, saddle, lower tectulum and abdominal neuromere (Berg et al., 2025). It sends output to the ipsilateral accessory mesothoracic neuropil, flange and T1 leg neuropil, the contralateral accessory mesothoracic neuropil and flange, and the gnathal ganglion, saddle, lower tectulum and abdominal neuromere (Berg et al., 2025). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025).</owl:annotatedTarget>
