        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Adult descending neuron of the posterior brain of the DNpe039 group (Berg et al., 2025). It belongs to the SMPpv2 ventral hemilineage (Berg et al., 2025). It receives input in the ipsilateral accessory mesothoracic neuropil, superior lateral protocerebrum, gorget, vest, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, posterior lateral protocerebrum, superior clamp, inferior clamp, cantle and T1 leg neuropil, and the gnathal ganglion, inferior bridge, saddle and lower tectulum (Berg et al., 2025). It sends output to the ipsilateral accessory mesothoracic neuropil, vest, flange and T1 leg neuropil, and the gnathal ganglion, saddle, lower tectulum and intermediate tectulum (Berg et al., 2025). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="http://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2020-07-30T12:00:00Z</terms:date>
        <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>fly_anatomy.ontology</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>CL306</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>DNxn131</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:20001011</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:comment>Cell type identified in multiple EM datasets (Scheffer et al., 2020; Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Marin et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025). Synapse locations are given where each cell of this type in neuprint has at least 10 connections. Hemilineage information from neuprint, though original source not clear.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>adult descending neuron of the posterior brain DNpe039</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
