        <obo:IAO_0000115>Adult descending neuron of the posterior brain of the DNpe020 group (Berg et al., 2025). It receives input in the gnathal ganglion, gorget, vest, posterior lateral protocerebrum, inferior clamp, inferior bridge, superior posterior slope, inferior posterior slope, saddle, flange, cantle, T1 leg neuropil, T3 leg neuropil, lower tectulum and abdominal neuromere (Berg et al., 2025). It sends output to the gnathal ganglion, inferior posterior slope, haltere neuropil, T1 leg neuropil, T2 leg neuropil, T3 leg neuropil, neck neuropil, lower tectulum, intermediate tectulum and abdominal neuromere (Berg et al., 2025). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="http://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705"/>
        <terms:date rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime">2020-07-30T12:00:00Z</terms:date>
