        <owl:annotatedTarget>Adult descending neuron of the posterior brain of the DNpe027 group (Berg et al., 2025). It receives input in the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe, superior medial protocerebrum, vest, wedge, crepine, antler, superior posterior slope and inferior posterior slope, and the gnathal ganglion, inferior bridge and intermediate tectulum (Berg et al., 2025). It sends output to the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe, vest, wedge, crepine, superior posterior slope, inferior posterior slope and T1 leg neuropil, and the gnathal ganglion, lower tectulum and intermediate tectulum (Berg et al., 2025). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025).</owl:annotatedTarget>
