        <owl:annotatedTarget>Adult descending neuron of the posterior brain of the DNpe025 group (Berg et al., 2025). It receives input in the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe, superior medial protocerebrum, mushroom body alpha&apos;-lobe, gorget, epaulette, vest, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, posterior lateral protocerebrum, superior clamp, inferior clamp, superior intermediate protocerebrum, superior posterior slope, T1 leg neuropil and T2 leg neuropil, and the cervical connective, gnathal ganglion, saddle and lower tectulum (Berg et al., 2025). It sends output to the ipsilateral accessory mesothoracic neuropil, superior posterior slope, T1 leg neuropil and T2 leg neuropil, and the gnathal ganglion, saddle and lower tectulum (Berg et al., 2025). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025).</owl:annotatedTarget>
