        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>VES029</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>FBbt:20003495</oboInOwl:id>
        <rdfs:comment>Cell type identified in multiple EM datasets (Scheffer et al., 2020; Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Marin et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025). Synapse locations are given where each cell of this type in neuprint has at least 10 connections.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>adult descending neuron of the outside anterior cluster DNde002</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FBbt_20003495"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>Adult descending neuron of the outside anterior cluster of the DNde002 group (Berg et al., 2025). It receives input in the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe, antennal lobe, gorget, epaulette, vest, inferior clamp, wedge, antler, superior posterior slope, flange, T1 leg neuropil and T2 leg neuropil, and the cervical connective, ventral nerve cord, gnathal ganglion, inferior bridge and saddle (Berg et al., 2025). It sends output to the ipsilateral vest, T1 leg neuropil and T2 leg neuropil, and the ventral nerve cord, gnathal ganglion and inferior bridge (Berg et al., 2025). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025).</owl:annotatedTarget>
