        <owl:annotatedTarget>Adult descending neuron of the anterior ventral brain of the DNbe007 group (Berg et al., 2025). It receives input in the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe, antennal lobe, vest, posterior lateral protocerebrum, inferior clamp, wedge, superior posterior slope, flange, T1 leg neuropil, T2 leg neuropil and T3 leg neuropil, and the gnathal ganglion, inferior bridge, saddle and abdominal neuromere (Berg et al., 2025). It sends output to the ipsilateral antennal lobe, vest, posterior lateral protocerebrum, inferior clamp, wedge, superior posterior slope, T1 leg neuropil, T2 leg neuropil and T3 leg neuropil, and the gnathal ganglion, inferior bridge, saddle, intermediate tectulum and abdominal neuromere (Berg et al., 2025). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024; Berg et al., 2025).</owl:annotatedTarget>
